  "prompt": "I am a third year mu engineering student. I have one kt in semester 2 will I get grace?",
  "response": "The policies regarding grace marks can vary significantly between universities and even between different departments within the same university. Generally, grace marks are awarded under specific conditions, often intended to help students pass a course when they are very close to the passing mark.\n\nTo determine whether you will receive grace marks for your backlog (KT) in semester 2, you should:\n\n1. **Check Your University Handbook:** Most universities have guidelines regarding grace marks. This information might be available online or in an academic handbook.\n\n2. **Contact Your Department:** Reach out to your department's academic coordinator or faculty advisor. They can provide information regarding your specific situation.\n\n3. **Look for Announcements:** Sometimes universities issue announcements regarding grace marks at the end of a semester or during exam results.\n\n4. **Discuss with Peers:** Fellow students who have been in a similar situation may also know about the university's policies regarding grace.\n\nMake sure to gather all the necessary information to understand your options and any potential consequences for your academic standing.",
